The paper proposes a novel saliency detection method for stereoscopic images, which involves evaluating the reliability of depth maps, introducing depth information into graph construction, and using multiple cues for saliency detection. This work is primarily focused on computer vision (CV) and graphics (GR), as it deals with image processing and analysis. Additionally, the use of machine learning (ML) and artificial intelligence (AI) techniques for saliency detection suggests that cs.AI is also a likely sub-category. The use of multiple cues and the integration of saliency maps suggest that the paper may also be relevant to multimedia (MM) and machine learning (LG) sub-categories.
